# Go Standards

- Read the owning package and nearby tests before editing.
- Keep package APIs narrow; prefer package-local helpers.
- Use explicit errors with useful context.
- Do not log secrets, auth headers, kubeconfig contents, web config secrets,
  registry tokens, or secret-manager values.
- Preserve mockability through existing wrapper packages.
- Run `make lint`, `make check-fmt`, and targeted `go test` for changed Go
  packages.
